{
  "title":"WEBSITE DEVELOPMENT — LEVEL 3 EXAMINATION",
   "description":"Total Questions: 50 | Total Marks: 100",
   "timeLimit":60,
   "passingScore":70,
   "sections":[
      {
         "name":"A",
         "title":"SECTION A: MULTIPLE CHOICE (20 Questions — 1 mark each)",
         "description":"Choose the correct answer from the options provided.",
         "questions":[
            {
               "text":"Which keyboard shortcut is used to copy selected text?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"Ctrl + X","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + V","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + C","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + Z","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"What does the keyboard shortcut Ctrl + Z do?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"Redo an action","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"Save a file","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"Undo an action","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"Cut selected text","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which shortcut is used to select ALL content on a page?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"Ctrl + S","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + P","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + A","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + D","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"What is the correct HTML tag for the largest heading?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"<h6>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"<heading>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"<h1>","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"<head>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which HTML tag is used to create a hyperlink?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"<link>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"<href>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"<a>","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"<url>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"What does HTML stand for?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"High Text Markup Language","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"Hyper Transfer Markup Language","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"HyperText Markup Language","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"Home Tool Markup Language","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which HTML tag is used to insert an image on a webpage?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"<picture>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"<photo>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"<img>","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"<src>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"What does CSS stand for?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"Creative Style Sheets","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"Computer Style Sheets","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"Cascading Style Sheets","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"Colorful Style Sheets","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which CSS property is used to change the text color of an element?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"font-color","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"text-color","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"color","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"background-color","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which CSS property controls the size of text?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"text-size","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"font-weight","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"font-size","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"text-style","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"What is the correct HTML structure to start a webpage?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"<body><html><head>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"<head><html><body>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"<html><head><body>","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"<html><body><head>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which HTML tag is used to create an unordered list?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"<ol>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"<li>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"<ul>","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"<list>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which keyboard shortcut saves a file in most programs?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"Ctrl + P","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + S","isCorrect":true,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + A","isCorrect":false,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"Ctrl + N","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"B"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which CSS property is used to add space inside an element's border?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"margin","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"spacing","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"padding","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"border-space","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"What does the <title> tag do in HTML?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"Creates a heading on the page","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"Styles the page header","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"Sets the title shown in the browser tab","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"Adds a bold title inside the page body","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which CSS property is used to change the background color of a webpage?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"color","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"page-color","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"background-color","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"fill-color","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which HTML tag creates a paragraph?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"<text>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"<pg>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"<p>","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"<para>","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"What does the href attribute do in an anchor <a> tag?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"Sets the link color","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"Sets the link size","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"Specifies the URL the link goes to","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"Hides the link","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"Which CSS property makes text bold?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":"text-style: bold","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"font-style: bold","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"font-weight: bold","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"text-weight: bold","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            },
            {
               "text":"In CSS, how do you select an element with the id \"header\"?",
               "type":"multiple-choice",
               "points":1,
               "options":[
                  {"text":".header","isCorrect":false,"letter":"A"},
                  {"text":"*header","isCorrect":false,"letter":"B"},
                  {"text":"#header","isCorrect":true,"letter":"C"},
                  {"text":"@header","isCorrect":false,"letter":"D"}
               ],
               "correctAnswer":"C"
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "name":"B",
         "title":"SECTION B: TRUE OR FALSE (15 Questions — 1 mark each)",
         "description":"Write TRUE or FALSE for each statement.",
         "questions":[
            {
               "text":"The keyboard shortcut Ctrl + V is used to paste content.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"TRUE"
            },
            {
               "text":"HTML stands for Hyper Transfer Markup Language.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"FALSE"
            },
            {
               "text":"The <br> tag is used to insert a line break in HTML.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"TRUE"
            },
            {
               "text":"CSS can only be applied by writing it inside the HTML file and cannot be saved in a separate file.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"FALSE"
            },
            {
               "text":"The <h6> tag produces the largest heading in HTML.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"FALSE"
            },
            {
               "text":"Pressing Ctrl + A selects all content in a document or text area.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"TRUE"
            },
            {
               "text":"The <img> tag requires a closing tag like </img> in standard HTML5.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"FALSE"
            },
            {
               "text":"Margin in CSS adds space outside an element's border.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"TRUE"
            },
            {
               "text":"A webpage can only have one CSS style applied to it.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"FALSE"
            },
            {
               "text":"The <ol> tag creates an ordered (numbered) list in HTML.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"TRUE"
            },
            {
               "text":"Keyboard shortcuts help improve typing speed and efficiency when developing websites.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"TRUE"
            },
            {
               "text":"The background-color CSS property changes the color of text.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"FALSE"
            },
            {
               "text":"Every HTML document must have a <html>, <head>, and <body> tag.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"TRUE"
            },
            {
               "text":"In CSS, a class selector is written using a # symbol.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"FALSE"
            },
            {
               "text":"The <p> tag is used to define a paragraph in HTML.",
               "type":"true-false",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"TRUE"
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "name":"C",
         "title":"SECTION C: FILL IN THE BLANKS (10 Questions — 1 mark each)",
         "description":"Fill in the missing word(s) to complete each statement.",
         "questions":[
            {
               "text":"The keyboard shortcut used to undo an action is __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"Ctrl + Z"
            },
            {
               "text":"The full meaning of CSS is __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"Cascading Style Sheets"
            },
            {
               "text":"To create a hyperlink in HTML, you use the __________ tag.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"<a>"
            },
            {
               "text":"The CSS property used to change text size is __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"font-size"
            },
            {
               "text":"The HTML tag used to display the largest heading on a page is __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"<h1>"
            },
            {
               "text":"In CSS, to select all elements with the class name \"menu\", you write __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":".menu"
            },
            {
               "text":"The HTML attribute used inside the <img> tag to specify the image file path is __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"src"
            },
            {
               "text":"To paste content using a keyboard shortcut, you press __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"Ctrl + V"
            },
            {
               "text":"The CSS property that adds space between the content and the element's border is __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":"padding"
            },
            {
               "text":"An HTML file is saved with the file extension __________.",
               "type":"fill-in-blank",
               "points":1,
               "correctAnswer":".html"
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "name":"D",
         "title":"SECTION D: OPEN QUESTIONS (5 Questions — 3 marks each)",
         "description":"Answer the following questions in full sentences.",
         "questions":[
            {
               "text":"Explain why keyboard shortcuts are important when developing a website. Give TWO examples of shortcuts and what they do.",
               "type":"open-ended",
               "points":3,
               "correctAnswer":"Keyboard shortcuts are important in website development because they save time and improve efficiency, allowing developers to work faster without switching between the mouse and keyboard. Two examples are: Ctrl + C — Copies selected text or content; Ctrl + S — Saves the current file."
            },
            {
               "text":"Describe the basic structure of an HTML webpage. Name and explain the purpose of THREE key HTML tags used in the structure.",
               "type":"open-ended",
               "points":3,
               "correctAnswer":"An HTML webpage has a basic structure made up of three main tags: <html> — The root tag that wraps the entire webpage content; <head> — Contains meta information about the page such as the title and links to CSS files; <body> — Contains all the visible content that appears on the webpage, such as text, images, and links."
            },
            {
               "text":"What is the difference between margin and padding in CSS? Give an example of when you would use each one.",
               "type":"open-ended",
               "points":3,
               "correctAnswer":"Padding is the space between the content of an element and its border. For example, you would use padding to add space inside a button so the text does not touch the edges. Margin is the space outside the element's border, separating it from other elements. For example, you would use margin to create space between two paragraphs or between a heading and an image."
            },
            {
               "text":"Explain TWO ways you can apply CSS styles to an HTML webpage.",
               "type":"open-ended",
               "points":3,
               "correctAnswer":"Internal CSS — Written inside a <style> tag placed within the <head> section of the HTML file. This applies styles only to that specific page. External CSS — Written in a separate .css file and linked to the HTML page using the <link> tag in the <head> section. This allows the same styles to be applied to multiple pages."
            },
            {
               "text":"A student wants to create a simple webpage with a heading, a paragraph, and a link to another website. Write the basic HTML code they would need and briefly explain what each line does.",
               "type":"open-ended",
               "points":3,
               "correctAnswer":"<!DOCTYPE html><html>  <head>    <title>My First Page</title>  </head>  <body>    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>    <p>This is my first paragraph of text.</p>    <a href=\"https://www.google.com\">Click here to visit Google</a>  </body></html>"
            }
         ]
      }
   ]
}
